      "writtenOn": "2018-06-25T23:29:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: Curious why this can\u0027t just exist in GrPipeline, and be ignored if a dynamic array overrides it?\n\n  \"fScissorRectIfFixed\"\n\nI\u0027m probably just out of the loop on future plans, but it would make less params to pass around.",
      "revId": "ccf89f45387c23e8a4689e961a7f3d7b6f5c3c61",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d31fa975_1e4b2bde",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrPipeline.h",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 90,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-26T13:16:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Most of the time the scissor is not used. As we make more rarely used things dynamic (e.g. window rects) and remove arrays with fixed storage pipelines can get slimmer at the cost of recording one extra pointer per mesh array draw. I\u0027m hoping this may give us better CPU cache performance.",
      "parentUuid": "2f2dc170_61922459",
      "revId": "ccf89f45387c23e8a4689e961a7f3d7b6f5c3c61",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
